The '''brown-headed thrush''' ('''''Turdus chrysolaus'''''), sometimes known as the '''brown thrush''',<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.birdlife.org/datazone/species/index.html?action=SpcHTMDetails.asp&sid=6402&m=0 |title=BirdLife species factsheet: Izu Thrush |access-date=2009-01-18 |archive-date=2009-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090103094455/http://www.birdlife.org/datazone/species/index.html?action=SpcHTMDetails.asp&sid=6402&m=0 }}</ref> is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Turdidae]]. It breeds in [[Sakhalin]], the [[Kuril Islands]] and [[Japan]]; it winters in south toward the [[Ryukyu Islands]], [[Taiwan]], [[Hainan]] and the northern [[Philippines]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is temperate [[forest]]s.

